quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,115,"And to Allāh belongs the east and the west. So wherever you [might] turn, there is the Face{1} of Allāh. Indeed, Allāh is all-Encompassing and Knowing.",footnotes:1:See footnote to 2:19.
  2,116,"They say, ",footnotes:1:Subḥānahu means "far exalted is He above all they falsely attribute to Him."
  2,117,"Originator of the heavens and the earth. When He decrees a matter, He only says to it, "
  3,55,"[Mention] when Allāh said, "
  3,56,"And as for those who disbelieved, I will punish them with a severe punishment in this world and the Hereafter, and they will have no helpers."
  3,57,"But as for those who believed and did righteous deeds, He will give them in full their rewards, and Allāh does not like the wrongdoers."